{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.40",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 40,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 40",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 40 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:1",
      "text": "And the Lord God answered Job, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:2",
      "text": "Will any one pervert judgment with the Mighty One? and he that reproves God, let him return it for answer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:3",
      "text": "And Job answered and said to the Lord,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:4",
      "text": "Why do I yet plead? being rebuked even while reproving the Lord: hearing such things, whereas I am nothing: and what shall I answer to these arguments? I will lay my hand upon my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:5",
      "text": "I have spoken once; but I will not do so a second time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:6",
      "text": "And the Lord yet again answered and spoke to Job out of the cloud, saying,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:7",
      "text": "Nay, gird up now thy loins like a man; and I will ask thee, and do thou answer me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:8",
      "text": "Do not set aside my judgment: and dost thou think that I have dealt with thee in any other way, than that thou mightest appear to be righteous?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:9",
      "text": "Hast thou an arm like the Lord's? or dost thou thunder with a voice like his?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:10",
      "text": "Assume now a lofty bearing and power; and clothe thyself with glory and honour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:11",
      "text": "And send forth messengers with wrath; and lay low every haughty one.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:12",
      "text": "Bring down also the proud man; and consume at once the ungodly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:13",
      "text": "And hide them together in the earth; and fill their faces with shame.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:14",
      "text": "Then will I confess that thy right hand can save thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:15",
      "text": "But now look at the wild beasts with thee; they eat grass like oxen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:16",
      "text": "Behold now, his strength is in his loins, and his force is in the navel of his belly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:17",
      "text": "He sets up his tail like a cypress; and his nerves are wrapped together.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:18",
      "text": "His sides are sides of brass; and his backbone is as cast iron.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:19",
      "text": "This is the chief of the creation of the Lord; made to be played with by his angels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:20",
      "text": "And when he has gone up to a steep mountain, he causes joy to the quadrupeds in the deep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:21",
      "text": "He lies under trees of every kind, by the papyrus, and reed, and bulrush.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:22",
      "text": "And the great trees make a shadow over him with their branches, and so do the bushes of the field.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:23",
      "text": "If there should be a flood, he will not perceive it; he trusts that Jordan will rush up into his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:24",
      "text": "Yet one shall take him in his sight; one shall catch him with a cord, and pierce his nose.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:25",
      "text": "But wilt thou catch the serpent with a hook, and put a halter about his nose?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:26",
      "text": "Or wilt thou fasten a ring in his nostril, and bore his lip with a clasp?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:27",
      "text": "Will he address thee with a petition? softly, with the voice of a suppliant?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:28",
      "text": "And will he make a covenant with thee? and wilt thou take him for a perpetual servant?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:29",
      "text": "And wilt thou play with him as with a bird? or bind him as a sparrow for a child?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:30",
      "text": "And do the nations feed upon him, and the nations of the Phœnicians share him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.31",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:31",
      "text": "And all the ships come together would not be able to bear the mere skin of his tail; neither shall they carry his head in fishing-vessels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.40.32",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:32",
      "text": "But thou shalt lay thy hand upon him once, remembering the war that is waged by his mouth; and let it not be done any more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
